Introduction: - The Centrally Sponsored Scheme for Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS), funded by the World Bank, is being implemented in the State from the year 2021-22. The scheme is funded by the Central Government and the State Government in the ratio of 60:40 respectively. Reference No. By order 1, the Central Government has deposited the second instalment of the current financial year for the component of Scheduled Castes Sub-Plan in the Consolidated Fund of the State. The proposal for devolution of this fund and its corresponding State share is referred to Reference No. 2 has been submitted to the government. A proposal to approve it was under consideration of the government.
